cocksfoot fever
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:the flood of enthusiastic growers and harvesters of cocksfoot into Banks Peninsula and other parts of Canterbury in the 1870s to 1930s.
Origin:[none]
